VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'able to do forward slash and then memory to be able to bring it up and edit it. You\'ll be able to see it\'s got this automatic memory that it can turn on. So every time you chat with it, it learns your preferences, what you want for'

[16:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'good, what you want for bad, of course, what you\'re looking to achieve, everything like this as we go through. We can also turn a brand new feature called auto dream on, and what this means is every now and again it\'s going'

[16:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to go through and store some more information so that you can reference it in future projects as you need. Now if you\'re serious about AI, come join us in the AI Edge on School. It\'s completely free to get started, hundreds of members all over the world. There\'s a full'

[16:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'masterclass section, templates you can grab and use straight away. No fluff, no algorithms, no ads. Link and QR code are on screen now, or just simply check the description and you\'ll see it there. Flags. These are additional commands'

[17:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that we want to give Claude at the start to tell it how it should operate. So for example, we can do Claude dash dash and then model, and then we\'ll be able to say exactly the model we want it to use.'

[17:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So for example, I would type claude-opus-4-6. This is going to start it up using that specific model if we hadn\'t already set it. Another one is we can come through'

[17:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and do claude-p, and you\'re able to use these in the command as well. So for example here, if you say hi there and then do dash p, all of these flags will work in there as well. And then after this, all you need'

[17:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to do is type the command name you want it to execute. So for example, we need the crow marks to tell it what we want. We could say build me a landing page for a consulting business. So now what it will do is if I execute this, it\'s going'

[18:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
